"content":"Layer 2 (扩展层):"},"38":{"id":"/notes/misc-34","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"建立在Layer 1之上的扩展解决方案"},"39":{"id":"/notes/misc-35","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"在链外处理大量交易，定期将结果提交到Layer 1"},"40":{"id":"/notes/misc-36","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"继承Layer 1安全性，同时提高性能、降低费用"},"41":{"id":"/notes/misc-37","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Rollup (卷叠技术):"},"42":{"id":"/notes/misc-38","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Layer 2的主要实现方式之一，与侧链(Sidechains)等非Rollup等方案相比，安全性较高"},"43":{"id":"/notes/misc-39","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"将多笔交易\"打包\"处理后，只向主链提交概要数据"},"44":{"id":"/notes/misc-40","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"分两种类型："},"45":{"id":"/notes/misc-41","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Optimistic Rollup (乐观卷叠): 假设交易有效，有争议期(通常7天)，如Optimism、Arbitrum"},"46":{"id":"/notes/misc-42","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"ZK-Rollup (零知识卷叠): 使用数学证明验证交易有效性，无需争议期，如zkSync、StarkNet"},"47":{"id":"/notes/misc-43","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"通俗比喻：如果把区块链比作交通系统"},"48":{"id":"/notes/misc-44","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Layer 1 是主干道：安全但容易拥堵"},"49":{"id":"/notes/misc-45","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Layer 2 是快速辅路：分流主干道交通"},"50":{"id":"/notes/misc-46","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"Rollup 是公交车：一次运送多人，只占一个车位的空间"},"51":{"id":"/notes/misc-47","page_id":"/notes/misc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/misc","content":"大多数 Shell 里，身份提示符$表示的是当前用户，#表示的是超级用户"},"52":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","type":"page","content":"中国法律位阶","tags":[],"url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law"},"53":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-0","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"对中国法律位阶的概述"},"54":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-1","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"参考资料"},"55":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-2","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"中国大陆的法律体系，按照效力位阶，可大致分为以下几个层级：宪法、法律、行政法规、地方性法规、规章。宪法是根本大法，具有最高的法律效力，其他法律都不能与宪法相抵触。\n以下是具体层级及其制定机关："},"56":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-3","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"宪法:\n《中华人民共和国宪法》是国家的根本大法，是其他一切法律的立法依据和基础。"},"57":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-4","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"法律:\n由全国人民代表大会(全国人大)及其常务委员会制定，如《中华人民共和国民法典》、《中华人民共和国刑法》等。"},"58":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-5","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"行政法规:\n由国务院制定，是对法律的具体化和补充，如《中华人民共和国食品安全法实施条例》。"},"59":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-6","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"地方性法规:\n由省级和设区的市级人民代表大会及其常务委员会制定，在各自的行政区域内施行，如《上海市生活垃圾管理条例》。"},"60":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-7","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","content":"规章:\n包括部门规章和地方政府规章，部门规章由国务院各部委制定，地方政府规章由地方各级人民政府制定。\n此外，还有一些特殊类型的法律，如自治条例和单行条例，它们在民族自治地方和经济特区具有特殊法律地位。法律效力层级的高低，决定了在具体适用法律时的优先顺序，下位法必须服从上位法。"},"61":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-8","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"中华人民共和国法律位阶 - 维基百科"},"62":{"id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law-9","page_id":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/civil-service/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"法律位阶 - 百度百科"},"63":{"id":"/notes/civil-service","page_id":"/notes/civil-service","type":"page","content":"行测笔记","tags":[],"url":"/notes/civil-service"},"64":{"id":"/notes/coding","page_id":"/notes/coding","type":"page","content":"Hello Code!","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding"},"65":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"page","content":"认识数据库","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse"},"66":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-0","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据","content":"数据"},"67":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-1","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库","content":"数据库"},"68":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-2","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库系统","content":"数据库系统"},"69":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-3","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库管理系统","content":"数据库管理系统"},"70":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-4","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#结论","content":"结论"},"71":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-5","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","content":"数据库中常见的基本概念如下。"},"72":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-6","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据","content":"数据是对客观事物、事件的记录与描述，也是对客观事物的逻辑归纳。数据可以是连续的，如声音、图像等，也可以是离散的，如符号、文字等。"},"73":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-7","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库","content":"数据库（Database，DB）是存储在计算机内、有组织的、可共享的相关数据的集合，这种集合按一定的数据模型组织、描述并长期存储，同时能够以安全可靠的方法对数据进行检索。"},"74":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-8","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库系统","content":"数据库系统（Database System，DBS）是指在计算机系统中引入数据库后的系统。它主要由数据库、数据库用户、计算机硬件系统和计算机软件系统（含数据库管理系统）等几部分组成。"},"75":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-9","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库管理系统","content":"数据库管理系统（Database Management System，DBMS）是指建立、运用、管理和维护数据库，并对数据库进行统一控制的系统软件。"},"76":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-10","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#数据库管理系统","content":"常见的数据库管理系统有 SQL Server、Oracle、MySQL、Access等。"},"77":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-11","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#结论","content":"Data < DB < DBMS < DBS"},"78":{"id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse-12","page_id":"/notes/coding/learn-databse","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/learn-databse#结论","content":"注意：DBMS 是 DBS 的必要组成部分，没有 DBMS 的 DBS 在实际中是不存在的。"},"79":{"id":"/notes/coding/package-json","page_id":"/notes/coding/package-json","type":"page","content":"什么是 package.json","tags":[],"url":"/notes/coding/package-json"},"80":{"id":"/notes/coding/package-json-0","page_id":"/notes/coding/package-json","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/coding/package-json","content":"package.json 是 npm 等前端包管理器生成的一份文件，其中包含许多元信息。"},"81":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"page","content":"写给学生的建议","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students"},"82":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-0","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"Advice for students 的译文"},"83":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-1","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"通用建议"},"84":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-2","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#optimizing-for-ikigai--alignment","content":"optimizing for ikigai & alignment."},"85":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-3","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"ikigai（存在的意义）"},"86":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-4","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"对齐感（Alignment）"},"87":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-5","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#打好身心健康的基础","content":"打好身心健康的基础"},"88":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-6","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"开展你热爱的课余项目"},"89":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-7","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上"},"90":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-8","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"building a habit and love of reading"},"91":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-9","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"不要做一个“NPC”！"},"92":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-10","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#常见问题与解答","content":"常见问题与解答"},"93":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-11","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#other-relevant-quotes-captured-by-much-better-writers","content":"Other relevant quotes captured by much better writers"},"94":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-12","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"title: 天明注"},"95":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-13","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"这是一篇译文，原文为 Stephen Wu 于 2024 年 9 月发表的 Advice for students。Stephen\n曾经在 Facebook 工作，现为 Notion 数据库团队的软件工程师。我在推特偶然看到他的主页并读到此文，深受启发，遂翻译分享。以下正文中的「我」均指原作者 Stephen Wu，如有歧义请以原文为准。"},"96":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-14","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"一些适合学生的通用建议"},"97":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-15","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"这些建议主要面向那些对在现代科技公司担任技术岗位感兴趣的计算机专业大学生，不过，其中很多内容对其他人也同样适用。"},"98":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-16","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","content":"常见的技术岗位有：软件工程师、产品经理、数据科学家、数据工程师或产品设计师等。"},"99":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-17","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"我对学生们的一贯建议可以总结为以下几点："},"100":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-18","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"探索生命的意义（ikigai），并寻求目标与内心的一致性。"},"101":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-19","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"打好心理与身体健康的基础。"},"102":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-20","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"开展你热爱的课余项目，并与志同道合的伙伴一起完成。"},"103":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-21","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"在职业发展上做出「明智的」投入。"},"104":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-22","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"让阅读成为一种习惯，也成为一种热爱。"},"105":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-23","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"不要像 NPC 那样随波逐流、缺乏思考！"},"106":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-24","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"关于建议的一点说明"},"107":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-25","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"建议总是依赖于特定语境，也往往是简化的表达，因此并不一定适用于每个人。"},"108":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-26","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"接纳那些与你产生共鸣的建议，并时常回顾；无法产生共鸣的也无需强求。"},"109":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-27","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"多接触不同的资源，广泛阅读各种想法！"},"110":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-28","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"人们常用这样一幅维恩图来形象地解释 ikigai（存在的意义）："},"111":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-29","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"找到你的 ikigai，意味着找到你热爱的事、你擅长的事、这个世界需要的事、以及能为你带来收入的事，这四者的交集。"},"112":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-30","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你热爱的事：是那些你在从事时感到真正的乐趣与激情的工作。"},"113":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-31","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你能获得报酬的事：是那些能为你带来外在回报，有助于生活与财务的工作。"},"114":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-32","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你擅长的事：你的技能与这类工作高度契合，而且你也有持续提升的兴趣。"},"115":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-33","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"这个世界需要的事：你能为他人创造价值，并感受到自己正在为社会或社群做出贡献。"},"116":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-34","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"在我与人们探讨职业满足感时，我发现最快乐的人，往往在这四个方面都达到了很高的程度。"},"117":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-35","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你也可以从另一个角度思考：寻找那些既能激发你内在热情，又能带来外在回报的机会。\n在职业生涯的早期阶段，你也许更应该关注成长空间和学习潜力。"},"118":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-36","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"通常来说，那些兼具内外动机的事情——既让你发自内心地热爱，又带来现实回报——你越有动力去做好，它们成功的可能性也越大。"},"119":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-37","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"举几个例子："},"120":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-38","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我在做一个我热爱的课余项目，它很有意义，同时还能帮助我学习 React。"},"121":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-39","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我正在实习，这份工作一方面帮我赚取学费，另一方面让我学到不少新东西。"},"122":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-40","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我花时间和我很敬佩的人相处，从他们身上学到很多。"},"123":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-41","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我的工作把我热爱的艺术与设计结合在一起，比如在 Figma 这样的公司工作。"},"124":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-42","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"理想情况下，几年后你可以达到这样的状态："},"125":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-43","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我在从事我热爱的工作，和我喜欢的人共事，参与的是与我价值观一致的项目。这份工作既让我不断成长，又能满足我的财务和个人目标。"},"126":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-44","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"要实现这样的状态，你可能需要有意识地做出一些努力，比如："},"127":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-45","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"主动进入新环境：寻找朋友、工作、俱乐部或项目；"},"128":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-46","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"培养良好的环境：建立习惯、主动提问、深化关系；"},"129":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-47","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"塑造积极的心态：培养感恩、自我记录、持续阅读；"},"130":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-48","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"为理想工作做好准备：投入于职业成长相关的行动（详见下文）。"},"131":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-49","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"在你参与某项活动时，不妨问问自己："},"132":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-50","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"我是否真心感到兴奋和投入？"},"133":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-51","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"我是否正与那些我敬佩、希望向他们学习的人共处？"},"134":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-52","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"这里的氛围是否让我感到自在？是否符合我的价值观？"},"135":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-53","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"这条路是否有助于我未来的发展，或者能让我成长？"},"136":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-54","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"如果以上问题你都无法肯定回答，那么这很可能是一个「价值观未对齐」的预警信号。"},"137":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-55","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"此时你需要认真地反思："},"138":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-56","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"我做这件事，是因为我真心想做，还是因为别人告诉我应该做？"},"139":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-57","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"我是因为觉得这条路是默认的选项、难以改变，才走上这条路的吗？"},"140":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-58","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#对齐感alignment","content":"随着时间推移，你会逐渐建立起一种更敏锐的「感知雷达」，帮助你判断哪些事情与你对齐、哪些没有。\n这种直觉将引导你走向更契合自我、更幸福、更充实的生活。🙂"},"141":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-59","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#打好身心健康的基础","content":"这意味着："},"142":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-60","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#打好身心健康的基础","content":"均衡饮食 🙂"},"143":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-61","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#打好身心健康的基础","content":"保证充足的锻炼和睡眠"},"144":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-62","page_id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students#打好身心健康的基础","content":"接受心理治疗、按时就医、合理使用药物"},"145":{"id":"/notes/geek-lab/advice-for-students-63"